Description: Rest on the flight into Egypt, with the Holy Family in a landscape, Joseph watering the donkey at the left, with the infant St John the Baptist leaning over the Child, at the right a wooden shelter in front of antique ruins Etching
Curator's comments: Acquired as after a design by Titian.
Acquisition notes: The 208 items in the 1950 purchase from the Liechtenstein collection consisted of Italian prints. They were views of Rome; prints after Titian; portraits of Roman Emperors; and various other prints after Venetian artists.
